Today I went in and bought a caramel macchiato during the evening. Parking here is really bad but the coffee was worse. It was disgusting. I was already in my car and had to pick up my son , it took me 10 mins to return and I explained to the guy that was there that the coffee was really bad and if he could make me another coffee. I put the cup full on the counter. He said that he could not  because I had already tasted the coffee and 10 mins had passed. I asked to speak with a manager and he laughed and told me to come back in 2 days when a manager was in. I buy a lot of coffee from DD and order on Uber but I won’t anymore! Especially because of the way I was treated!!

So this has been a long standing establishment and one of my favorites for the past 10 years. With that being said once they transitioned over to their current owners this place has gotten horrible. The service sucks and the servers need to become more knowledgeable about how to make coffee. I went in today to order a caramel latte the girl takes over 10 mins to present me with a latte (i was the only person in the line when i walked in) that looked as if it was nothing whatsoever but milk no coffee at all the entire drink was as white as the whipped cream that i asked her to put on top. Which by the way she charged me $0.30 for, i know right? No other DD that i have visited has ever done this not even in the city. I told her it was too white to remake it it's not supposed to be that light. She acts as if she doesn't understand what I'm telling her so i call her partner he's trying to justify this milk concoction which I'm not going for i ask him to just remake me another one. As I'm discussing him making my new drink she comes with my money back, and no they do no remake my drink. What type of customer service is this as far as i know the customer is always right i wasn't yelling screaming or being rude i just asked that they make me a new drink and they refused. I give this establishment 1 star for terrible customer service and them needing to train their employee's better. Needless to say after this experience i won't be spending my money in there, there are to many other DD's in the area that value their customers.

The best Dunkin' in this area. We were attended by a Nathaniel he was friendly and he did not mess up our order. Also, my boys like their old fashioned doughnuts to be heated. They obliged and they warmed the doughnuts without a problem. Usually, the other Dunkin in Myrtle ave are rude.
